---
import "@/styles/global.css";
import BaseLayout from "@/components/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  SEOTitle="EconAI | PrincipalAI"
  SEODescription="AI-supported research and policy intelligence for evidence, analysis, and defensible decision-making."
>
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#071f3f] via-[#123f86] to-[#dbe8ff] px-8 py-24 text-white">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-blue-100">
        EconAI
      </p>
      <h1 class="max-w-4xl font-serif text-5xl font-bold leading-tight sm:text-6xl">
        Research and policy intelligence for evidence-based decisions.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-relaxed text-blue-50">
        EconAI helps teams find, compare, synthesise, and apply evidence across complex information environments. It is designed for organisations that need faster analysis without weakening professional judgement, traceability, or analytical quality.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main>
    <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600">
            The problem
          </p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">
            Evidence is abundant. Decision-ready insight is scarce.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          <p>
            Policy, economic, infrastructure, and regulatory decisions often rely on large volumes of reports, papers, datasets, models, and internal knowledge. The challenge is not only finding information, but understanding its relevance, quality, assumptions, and implications.
          </p>
          <p>
            EconAI provides an intelligence layer that helps analysts move from search to synthesis, and from synthesis to practical decision support.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-gray-50 px-8 py-20">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600">
          What it supports
        </p>
        <h2 class="max-w-3xl font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">
          Built for professional research and advisory workflows.
        </h2>

        <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Evidence retrieval</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Locate relevant information across documents, reports, and structured knowledge sources.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Source comparison</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Compare findings, assumptions, methods, and conclusions across multiple sources.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Policy synthesis</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Prepare structured summaries that support policy advice, business cases, and strategic reviews.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-md bg-white p-7 shadow-sm ring-1 ring-gray-200">
            <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900">Decision support</h3>
            <p class="mt-4 text-gray-700">
              Translate evidence into clear implications for decisions, options, risks, and trade-offs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="px-8 py-20 bg-white">
      <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-12 lg:grid-cols-2">
        <div>
          <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wide text-blue-600">
            Why PrincipalAI
          </p>
          <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight text-gray-900">
            AI shaped by economics, policy, and applied modelling.
          </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-700">
          <p>
            EconAI is not a generic chatbot. It is designed around professional analytical workflows where evidence quality, context, assumptions, and judgement matter.
          </p>
          <p>
            PrincipalAI combines AI capability with Principal Economics’ experience in economics, infrastructure, energy, transport, health, climate, and public policy.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="bg-[#071f3f] px-8 py-20 text-white">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl text-center">
        <h2 class="mx-auto max-w-4xl font-serif text-4xl font-bold leading-tight">
          Build research intelligence around your organisation’s decisions.
        </h2>
        <p class="mx-auto mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-blue-50">
          Talk to PrincipalAI about deploying EconAI for evidence synthesis, policy intelligence, and analytical workflow support.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/contact"
          class="mt-8 inline-block rounded-md bg-blue-600 px-7 py-3 font-semibold text-white hover:bg-blue-700"
        >
          Request a demonstration
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
